    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S1_Title">Welcome to ClickyKeys!</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S1_Body">Let me walk you through a quick tutorial.\nFeel free to interact with the app at any time — click Next to continue.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S2_Title">Panels</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S2_Body">These are your display panels — the main feature of ClickyKeys.\nEach panel counts presses of its assigned key.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S3_Title">Editing a panel</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S3_Body">Left-click any panel to open the editor and assign a key to it.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S3_Hint">👆 Click the panel to try it</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S4_Title">Description and key</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S4_Body">Type a name in the Description field.\nThen click Input and press the key you want to track.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S5_Title">Saving changes</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S5_Body">Confirm your changes with the green ✔ button, or discard them with the red ✖.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S6_Title">Appearance</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S6_Body">Open the Appearance tab to customise colours, grid size, fonts, and more.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S6_Hint">👆 Appearance button</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S7_Title">Applying changes</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S7_Body">Click Save at the bottom of Appearance to save your current layout and override current profile.\nUnsaved changes will be discarded after closing Appearance tab.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S8_Title">Creating a new layout</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S8_Body">Click Save As at the bottom of Appearance to save your layout under a new name. Enter a new profile name and click Save.\nSaved profiles can be loaded from the Load tab.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S9_Title">Reset</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S9_Body">The Reset button (F12) clears all panel counters without changing their configuration or layout.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S9_Hint">👆 Reset button</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S10_Title">Display</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S10_Body">Hover the Display tab to reveal extra options:\n• Transparent mode — hides the background and toolbar, useful for streaming overlays.\n• Hide toolbar (F11) — collapses the toolbar.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S10_Hint">👆 Hover the Display tab</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S11_Title">Stats</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S11_Body">The Stats tab shows how many keys you've pressed in total.\nYour data is stored only on your local drive.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S11_Hint">👆 Stats button</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S12_Title">More</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S12_Body">Hover the More tab to reveal the Info tab and the Settings window.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S12_Hint">👆 Hover the More tab</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S13_Title">Settings</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S13_Body">The Settings window lets you configure the app: collecting uptime and key-press data, launching on system startup, starting minimized, and the interface language.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S13_Hint">👆 More tab ▸ Settings</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S14_Title">Info</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S14_Body">Visit the Info tab to learn more about the ClickyKeys project or watch this tutorial again.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S14_Hint">👆 More tab ▸ Info</sys:String>
